<div class="tw-p-2 tw-font-alt">
    {{!-- Trained / Basic skills flow into 1–3 width-responsive columns (#267).
         auto-fit makes the grid track count follow the PANEL width (not the
         viewport): it collapses to a single column on a narrow sheet and caps
         at three via the max(min-col, container/3) idiom (gap = 0.5rem ⇒ two
         gaps subtracted at the 3-column breakpoint). Floor is 10rem (down from
         14rem): the narrower floor lets columns reflow before text truncates —
         padding shrinks first as columns narrow, then the track count drops.
         Skills render from the flat `standard` list in row-major order rather
         than the old fixed two-array column split. --}}
    <div class="tw-grid tw-gap-2 tw-relative" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(max(10rem, calc((100% - 1rem) / 3)), 1fr));">
        {{#each skillLists.standard as |entry|}}
            {{> systems/wh40k-rpg/templates/actor/partial/skill-row.hbs entry=entry}}
        {{/each}}
    </div>

    {{!-- DH2e has no separate "Advanced Skills" tier; advancedUntrained is now empty and
         every standard skill renders in the responsive grid above. See issue #2. --}}
</div>
